1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,759
♪ I thought
I knew about brave ♪

2
00:00:08,759 --> 00:00:12,763
♪ I thought I knew
through and through ♪

3
00:00:12,763 --> 00:00:16,850
♪ It was all about
fighting a dragon ♪

4
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:20,229
♪ Crossing the Serpent River
blue, yeah ♪

5
00:00:20,229 --> 00:00:23,023
♪ And marching
into Castle Dark ♪

6
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:26,068
♪ It takes courage
but that's not hard ♪

7
00:00:26,068 --> 00:00:28,654
♪ Be the real you,
be the true you ♪

8
00:00:28,654 --> 00:00:33,408
♪ It's the bravest thing
you can do ♪

9
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:36,370
♪ The bravest knight ♪

10
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:38,997
[crackling]

11
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:43,001
♪ The bravest knight ♪

12
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:44,670
[roars]

13
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:46,755
[whooshing]

14
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:48,298
♪ Be the greatest ♪

15
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,425
♪ Be the bravest ♪

16
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:52,928
♪ Your own fairy‐tale ending ♪

17
00:00:52,928 --> 00:00:54,596
♪ The bravest knight ♪

18
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:56,765
♪

19
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:00,143
[tense instrumental music]

20
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:05,774
[slow melodic
instrumental music]

21
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:07,067
[water splashing]

22
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,610
[Nia] Whoo, whoo, whoo.

23
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,529
[Cedric] Nia!

24
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:15,117
♪

25
00:01:15,117 --> 00:01:20,497
Nia! Nia!

26
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:22,916
Hi, Dad!

27
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,751
There you are.

28
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,588
Are you ready for your lesson
in becoming a knight?

29
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:29,173
Always ready, Dad!

30
00:01:29,173 --> 00:01:30,841
Who am I battling?

31
00:01:30,841 --> 00:01:32,718
Oh, there's no battle.

32
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:35,095
Why do you always think
there's a battle?

33
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:37,639
Isn't that what being
a knight is all about?

34
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:41,476
Being a not‐yet‐knight
is about more than battling.

35
00:01:41,476 --> 00:01:43,896
Nia, today I am going
to teach you

36
00:01:43,896 --> 00:01:47,316
how to rescue someone
from the top of a tower.

37
00:01:47,316 --> 00:01:50,152
Prince Andrew has volunteered
to be saved.

38
00:01:50,152 --> 00:01:52,070
Hi, Nia!

39
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,238
Hi, Papa!

40
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:54,740
Can we hurry this up?

41
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:56,700
I have to be
at royal court soon.

42
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:59,536
Can't rush these things, Papa.

43
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:01,705
Shouldn't he be tied up
or something?

44
00:02:01,705 --> 00:02:07,503
I've collected some things
to help you build a ladder.

45
00:02:07,503 --> 00:02:10,005
It is best to take it
nice and slow‐‐

46
00:02:10,005 --> 00:02:12,674
Well, that's lucky.

47
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:15,135
Now, hold on, Nia.

48
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:18,639
You can't always trust
what you see.

49
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:22,226
Let me tell you a story
about a tower I once found.

50
00:02:22,226 --> 00:02:24,520
[Andrew]
Can we hurry this up?

51
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:27,439
Uh, a short story.

52
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:30,025
[Cedric narrating] I'd left
my home on the pumpkin farm

53
00:02:30,025 --> 00:02:34,696
and by now it was my third year
as a not‐yet‐knight.

54
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:36,865
Okay, it may have been
my second year

55
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:38,575
as a not‐yet‐knight.

56
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:41,787
The whole kingdom was in a panic
because a dragon

57
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:44,831
had broken all the villains
out of Fairy Jail

58
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,667
and now they were on the loose.

59
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,585
[Nia gasps]

60
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:51,171
[Nia] I thought dragons had been
banished from the kingdom.

61
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,173
[Cedric narrating]
All except one.

62
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:56,718
I was determined to do my part.

63
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,762
"Pleasant Path".

64
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:01,807
"Even More Pleasant Path".

65
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:04,935
Hm, if you can't trust a sign
then who can you trust?

66
00:03:04,935 --> 00:03:08,272
♪

67
00:03:08,272 --> 00:03:10,440
Hm, must be from a storm.

68
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:12,359
Whoo‐yah!

69
00:03:12,359 --> 00:03:16,029
[male voice] Who dares to try
and cross my tree?

70
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:17,739
You must stop and pay the fee.

71
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:19,533
Um, my name is Cedric?

72
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:20,701
[clears throat]

73
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:22,286
I'm a not‐yet‐knight.

74
00:03:22,286 --> 00:03:23,954
What's your name, tree?

75
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:26,039
[male voice]
I'm not a tree, I'm‐‐

76
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:27,666
[clears throat]

77
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:29,626
I am the troll
who keeps the way;

78
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:31,420
none shall pass who do not pay.

79
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,755
You want me to pay
to cross the tree?

80
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:35,632
Why wouldn't I just
walk around it?

81
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:37,342
[male voice] Well, um...

82
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:40,262
You see, the tree cannot
be walked around.

83
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:42,848
Uh, a better path cannot,
um... be found?

84
00:03:42,848 --> 00:03:45,309
Ooh...

85
00:03:45,309 --> 00:03:47,060
This isn't my regular job.

86
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,604
Hm, a tree troll.

87
00:03:48,604 --> 00:03:50,439
How'd you get so good
at rhyming?

88
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,232
You might say
it's in the timing.

89
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,609
[chuckling]

90
00:03:53,609 --> 00:03:55,777
And, uh, I'm not a tree troll.

91
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:57,321
What's your name?

92
00:03:57,321 --> 00:03:58,572
Grunt.

93
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,532
[Young Cedric grunts]

94
00:04:00,532 --> 00:04:02,242
No. No, my name is Grunt.

95
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,952
Oh...

96
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:08,415
So, what were you doing
under that tree?

97
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:10,751
I used to have a bridge.

98
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:14,588
And then one day...

99
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:16,548
[thunderous footsteps]

100
00:04:16,548 --> 00:04:19,968
...that villainous troll, Sturk,
came and took it from me.

101
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,553
[Sturk roaring]

102
00:04:21,553 --> 00:04:24,139
[screaming]

103
00:04:24,139 --> 00:04:25,891
I had to run away!

104
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:27,851
[screaming continues]

105
00:04:27,851 --> 00:04:29,978
By the time I got done rolling,

106
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:32,022
I didn't know where
I was anymore.

107
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:35,108
And now I'm a bridgeless troll!

108
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:37,903
Hm, Sturk.
I've heard of him.

109
00:04:37,903 --> 00:04:40,364
He's a big, gross,
smelly troll, right?

110
00:04:40,364 --> 00:04:43,867
Yeah, all that stuff,
but I still don't like him!

111
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,619
He's one of the villains

112
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:48,205
that the dragon
broke out of Fairy Jail.

113
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:49,998
[sobbing]

114
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:52,543
What am I gonna do?

115
00:04:52,543 --> 00:04:54,127
I have an idea.

116
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:56,129
You want your bridge back
from Sturk, right?

117
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:58,340
[blows nose loudly]
Right.

118
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,884
And I wanna become a brave
knight one day, right?

119
00:05:00,884 --> 00:05:02,553
I don't know!

120
00:05:02,553 --> 00:05:05,055
How am I supposed to know?
I just met you!

121
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:06,890
Well, it's true!

122
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:09,810
And I'm gonna do it by helping
you get your bridge back

123
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,395
and defeating Sturk myself!

124
00:05:11,395 --> 00:05:13,730
You...
You would‐‐ would help me?

125
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:16,233
Well, yeah.
It's kind of what I do.

126
00:05:16,233 --> 00:05:18,026
I accept.

127
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:19,695
Great.

128
00:05:19,695 --> 00:05:21,738
So, which direction
did you roll in from?

129
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:23,282
That's hard to say.

130
00:05:23,282 --> 00:05:25,033
I've been wandering
around for weeks.

131
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:27,452
I wish I would have known that
before I agreed‐‐

132
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:28,537
[Grunt] Too late!

133
00:05:28,537 --> 00:05:30,706
[Grunt laughing]

134
00:05:30,706 --> 00:05:33,208
[Cedric narrating] So Grunt
and I continued along together.

135
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:35,169
I was determined
to find his bridge.

136
00:05:35,169 --> 00:05:36,920
"Rockshire".

137
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,630
"Serpent River".

138
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:40,174
"Snow Mountain".

139
00:05:40,174 --> 00:05:42,551
Which one is‐‐

140
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:44,761
[Cedric] But it was becoming
painfully clear

141
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:47,014
that he really didn't
have any clue

142
00:05:47,014 --> 00:05:48,891
where we were going.

143
00:05:48,891 --> 00:05:51,852
Still, a not‐yet‐knight
never breaks their promise.

144
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:54,062
[woman screaming in distance]

145
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,814
Did you hear that?

146
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:57,774
[screaming continues]

147
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:02,821
Someone's in trouble, let's go!

148
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:04,990
You wanna run towards
the scream?

149
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,576
Hello, there!

150
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:09,620
I'm a not‐yet‐knight
and I'm here to help.

151
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:11,330
Are you trapped?

152
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:13,457
[woman] Mm‐hm.

153
00:06:13,457 --> 00:06:16,001
Were you put there
by an evil witch?

154
00:06:16,001 --> 00:06:17,711
[woman] Mm‐hm!

155
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:18,962
I knew it.

156
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:21,006
Never fear, we'll save you!

157
00:06:21,006 --> 00:06:23,509
But, how do we get up there?

158
00:06:23,509 --> 00:06:26,762
♪

159
00:06:26,762 --> 00:06:28,430
Well, that was lucky.

160
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,390
Yuck, bleh!
This hair looks gross.

161
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:32,935
[woman, raspy voice]
Are you really‐‐

162
00:06:32,935 --> 00:06:36,855
[high‐pitched voice] ...gonna
call something gross?

163
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:39,233
[Cedric] So, are you a princess?

164
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:40,943
Or a farmer's daughter?

165
00:06:40,943 --> 00:06:42,903
They're always getting
trapped in towers.

166
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:45,197
[squelching]

167
00:06:45,197 --> 00:06:46,490
[screaming]

168
00:06:46,490 --> 00:06:48,283
[maniacal laughter]

169
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:50,244
Did I forget to mention?

170
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:52,955
I'm actually Trulla,

171
00:06:52,955 --> 00:06:57,042
the wickedest witch
in the entire kingdom!

172
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:59,795
[cackling]

173
00:06:59,795 --> 00:07:01,547
I've seen wickeder.

174
00:07:01,547 --> 00:07:05,717
[gears grinding]

175
00:07:05,717 --> 00:07:09,137
[Cedric and Grunt screaming]

176
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,347
[heavy thud]

177
00:07:10,347 --> 00:07:12,224
Oof!

178
00:07:12,224 --> 00:07:14,643
[Trulla] Have fun being
stuck in my pit,

179
00:07:14,643 --> 00:07:16,812
never‐been‐knight!

180
00:07:16,812 --> 00:07:18,981
[laughing wickedly]

181
00:07:18,981 --> 00:07:21,900
That was unnecessary.

182
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:25,153
You fell for her tower rescue
trick too, huh?

183
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,780
Whoa, who are you?

184
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,532
I'm Maven.

185
00:07:28,532 --> 00:07:29,658
[gasps]

186
00:07:29,658 --> 00:07:30,993
Hey, is that a troll?

187
00:07:30,993 --> 00:07:32,327
Stop!

188
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:34,037
But... he's a troll.

189
00:07:34,037 --> 00:07:36,456
I am standing
right here.

190
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,458
No offense, but you are.

191
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,085
Grunt's with me.

192
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:42,337
Besides, we have bigger things
to focus on

193
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:45,048
like how we're gonna
get out of here.

194
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:47,217
All right, we'll trust you.

195
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:48,844
For now.

196
00:07:48,844 --> 00:07:50,804
How long have you been
stuck down here?

197
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:52,598
Longest one is Sebastian.

198
00:07:52,598 --> 00:07:54,016
He's been here four days.

199
00:07:54,016 --> 00:07:55,601
Which one is he?

200
00:07:55,601 --> 00:07:57,352
He's digging a tunnel.

201
00:07:57,352 --> 00:07:59,021
Has been since he got here.

202
00:07:59,021 --> 00:08:00,772
Fantastic!
How far has he gotten?

203
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:03,150
Ey, Sebastian!
How far are you?

204
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,610
At least two feet now.

205
00:08:04,610 --> 00:08:08,780
So, digging's
not gonna work.

206
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,199
What supplies do we have?

207
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:12,451
We have our swords.

208
00:08:12,451 --> 00:08:15,245
Although, Sebastian has ground
most of them down to the nub.

209
00:08:15,245 --> 00:08:17,039
Besides that,
all we have is mud.

210
00:08:17,039 --> 00:08:19,750
[laughing]

211
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,210
Look, Cedric.

212
00:08:21,210 --> 00:08:23,128
Mud‐pants.

213
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:24,880
That's it!

214
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,798
Grunt, you've just figured
out the plan.

215
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,634
Yeah?
Yeah, of course I did!

216
00:08:28,634 --> 00:08:29,968
Come on.

217
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,929
Wait, what is it?
What's the plan?

218
00:08:31,929 --> 00:08:34,973
♪

219
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:36,475
[screaming]

220
00:08:38,602 --> 00:08:40,395
[thud]

221
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:45,150
Be sure to say hello
to the others for me!

222
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,945
[Trulla laughing]

223
00:08:50,906 --> 00:08:53,867
What others?

224
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:57,663
Not the sharpest jouster
in the tournament, are you?

225
00:08:57,663 --> 00:09:01,041
The others down inside the‐‐

226
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:02,918
[gasping]

227
00:09:02,918 --> 00:09:04,253
Where did they go?

228
00:09:04,253 --> 00:09:05,838
♪

229
00:09:05,838 --> 00:09:08,006
But they were just here!

230
00:09:08,006 --> 00:09:09,424
And now you are!

231
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:10,968
Now!

232
00:09:10,968 --> 00:09:12,678
Take that, Trulla!

233
00:09:12,678 --> 00:09:13,929
[laughing]

234
00:09:13,929 --> 00:09:15,430
Get her!

235
00:09:15,430 --> 00:09:17,057
Yeah!

236
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:19,893
Yeah!

237
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:22,604
Are all trolls that good
at kicking dirt?

238
00:09:22,604 --> 00:09:25,315
I think that's a stereotype.

239
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:27,568
You and your pet troll
did this!

240
00:09:27,568 --> 00:09:29,778
You'll regret it!

241
00:09:29,778 --> 00:09:31,196
I have powerful‐‐

242
00:09:31,196 --> 00:09:34,199
[muffled grunting]

243
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:36,118
Let's get out of here

244
00:09:36,118 --> 00:09:38,871
before she causes
any more trouble.

245
00:09:38,871 --> 00:09:42,624
♪

246
00:09:42,624 --> 00:09:45,377
You'll all pay for this.

247
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:46,628
You'll pay!

248
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:48,547
Hey, Trulla!

249
00:09:48,547 --> 00:09:51,425
You got a little something
on the corner, there.

250
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:55,888
So, you're the one who captured
the escaped witch, eh?

251
00:09:55,888 --> 00:09:58,682
The Knights Declarant thank you
for your help.

252
00:09:58,682 --> 00:10:02,019
We all did it together,
the not‐yet‐knights and Grunt.

253
00:10:02,019 --> 00:10:04,104
I heard there was a troll.

254
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,023
Is it the same one

255
00:10:06,023 --> 00:10:09,651
who's been making people pay
to walk by trees?

256
00:10:09,651 --> 00:10:11,361
♪

257
00:10:11,361 --> 00:10:12,988
No, not Grunt.

258
00:10:12,988 --> 00:10:15,574
That doesn't sound
like him at all.

259
00:10:15,574 --> 00:10:17,951
Sir, I was wondering
if I could become

260
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:19,703
a part of the Knights Declarant.

261
00:10:19,703 --> 00:10:21,914
I could help you catch
more escaped villains.

262
00:10:21,914 --> 00:10:23,415
[chuckling patronizingly]

263
00:10:23,415 --> 00:10:25,000
You're adorable!

264
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,085
The Knights Declarant
are searching

265
00:10:27,085 --> 00:10:29,630
for the dragon
who let them all loose.

266
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:31,840
It's dangerous,
treacherous work,

267
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,634
and you're just a kid.

268
00:10:33,634 --> 00:10:35,677
And are you any closer
to finding her?

269
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:37,888
I don't have time to answer
your questions,

270
00:10:37,888 --> 00:10:39,932
I'm busy looking for the dragon.

271
00:10:39,932 --> 00:10:43,060
[knight] A little help?

272
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:47,064
[Cedric] That was the first time
that I tangled with a villain,

273
00:10:47,064 --> 00:10:49,525
but it wouldn't be the last.

274
00:10:49,525 --> 00:10:53,570
That day I learned that things
aren't always what they seem.

275
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:56,365
And, not to grab a rope
unless you're certain

276
00:10:56,365 --> 00:10:59,034
what's on the other end.

277
00:10:59,034 --> 00:11:02,913
So, Nia, do you understand now
why you can't‐‐

278
00:11:02,913 --> 00:11:04,248
Uh, Nia?

279
00:11:04,248 --> 00:11:05,749
[Nia] Got it, Dad.

280
00:11:05,749 --> 00:11:07,835
Can't trust the person
you're saving.

281
00:11:07,835 --> 00:11:11,296
That's why I tied Papa up
to ask him some questions.

282
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:13,090
Um, Cedric?

283
00:11:13,090 --> 00:11:15,467
Think you could give me
a little help here?

284
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:18,053
Uh, right.

285
00:11:18,053 --> 00:11:19,388
[scissors rasping]

286
00:11:19,388 --> 00:11:21,306
Trust no one!

287
00:11:21,306 --> 00:11:25,227
I'm not sure she got
the right lesson.

288
00:11:25,227 --> 00:11:26,603
Oh, she'll get there.

289
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:28,689
She has to.

290
